              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": {
                "text": "Dirt is waste, excrement, rubbish - but what then is soil? Is cleanliness next to godliness - or sterility? And in a throwaway society, does the battle against dirt depend on an exploited and half-seen underclass of cleaners?",
                "spans": []
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": {
                "text": "Published by Profile Books to coincide with Wellcome Collection's major exhibition 'Dirt', and lavishly illustrated with images from the Collection's archives, this provocative book features specially commissioned essays and a short graphic novel section on the significance and implications of dirt from the microbial level through to the environmental.",
                "spans": [
                  {
                    "start": 83,
                    "end": 89,
